<P>
   FAU _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ This could be the week that
Florida Atlantic University in Boca Raton gets the title of
research university, allowing it to expand its graduate programs,
compete for grant money and eventually collect higher tuition from
undergraduates. (Horine, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-HMO _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumers apparently aren't as upset
with the treatment they get from health maintenance organizations
as some thought they were. Eight months after Texas started a
landmark independent review program for consumers who want to
dispute HMO treatment denials, only 147 complaints have been filed
with the Texas Department of Insurance. (Golz, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE (l category)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL BLACK ARTS FESTIVAL
</P>
<P>
   NBAF-DRUMMER _ James Brown's timeless exhortation to ``give the
drummer some'' is nearly redundant when the percussionist in
question is Hamid Drake. At 42, the Chicago-based musician is an
emerging master whose versatile skills and quicksilver intuition
have made him one of the most in-demand collaborators in the
sometimes amorphous field of jazz and improvised music. He performs
July 16-17 as part of a three-day jazz summit, part of the NBAF.
(Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   NBAF-DRUMMER _ A roundup listing who else is playing in the jazz
summit, and what to expect from them. (Dollar, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   NBAF-LATEEF _ NBAF music program featuring Yusef Lateef
performing with ASO/Yoel Levi Wednesday night. (Dollar, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERDINNERS _ One day, ordering dinner over the Internet may be
easier than phoning the pizza joint down the street for a large
pie, hold the olives. That day is not here yet, as even Cybermeals
president Tim Glass will admit. But he believes that as technology
improves, it's coming. Already, computer users can place takeout or
delivery orders online for 200 metro Atlanta restaurants through
Seattle-based Cybermeals. (ELee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA
8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-SCHOOL _ Back to school fashion. (Ryan, Austin
American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   SPACECAMP _ 12-year-old Sam Sargent has just returned from the
Space Academy at NASA's training facility in Huntsville, Ala. He
had a wonderfully inspiring time and will write about his
experiences. (Sargent for the Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SPACECAMP-SIDE _ Factual sidebar about the camp, including its
purpose, activities, weeks of operation, cost, etc. HOLLOWAY 20.
(Holloway, Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   WEBCAM _ DAYTON, Ohio Homer Ramby credits the ``WayneCam'' with
an extra big turnout for this year's Wayne Twp. Volunteer Fire
Department Fish Fry. The camera, perched atop a telephone pole at
Miami and Main streets a block from the firehouse, uploads an image
of downtown Waynesville onto the Internet every 20 minutes, where
it can be seen by anyone sitting at a computer from Switzerland to
Swaziland. From small towns to hip urban watering holes, web cam
sites are proliferating on the Internet faster than the most
voracious cyberspace voyeurs can double-click. (DeBrosse/Tresslar,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Why is K the baseball symbol for strikeout? Why
do military jets fly higher than commercial jets? Where can we send
sympathy cards for Roy Rogers' death? And more questions from the
week's news Q &AMP; A. Moves in two parts. (Bessonette, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
