<P>
   NBAF-DRUMMER _ James Brown's timeless exhortation to ``give the
drummer some'' is nearly redundant when the percussionist in
question is Hamid Drake. At 42, the Chicago-based musician is an
emerging master whose versatile skills and quicksilver intuition
have made him one of the most in-demand collaborators in the
sometimes amorphous field of jazz and improvised music. He performs
July 16-17 as part of a three-day jazz summit, part of the NBAF.
(Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
