<P>
   CYBERDINNERS _ One day, ordering dinner over the Internet may be
easier than phoning the pizza joint down the street for a large
pie, hold the olives. That day is not here yet, as even Cybermeals
president Tim Glass will admit. But he believes that as technology
improves, it's coming. Already, computer users can place takeout or
delivery orders online for 200 metro Atlanta restaurants through
Seattle-based Cybermeals. (ELee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA
8 p.m. ET.
