<P>
   GMAC-RFC Picks Campbell Mithun
</P>
<P>
   GMAC-RFC in Bloomington, Minn., the investment arm of the
General Motors Acceptance Corp., which issues car loans and leases,
said Tuesday that it had named Campbell Mithun Esty in Minneapolis
to handle its marketing account, which had been handled in-house.
Billings were estimated at $8 million to $10 million. Campbell
Mithun, which is majority-owned by the Interpublic Group of
Companies, was awarded the assignment after a four-month review
that had been narrowed to that agency and one other finalist,
Clarion Marketing and Communications Group in Greenwich, Conn.,
part of MacManus Group.
</P>
<P>
   Accounts
</P>
<P>
   _ C&AMP;H Sugar, Crockett, Calif., to Media That Works, Cincinnati,
to handle media planning and buying on its account, which had been
handled by Goldberg Moser O'Neill, San Francisco. Billings were
estimated at $3 million. Hallberg, Schireson &AMP; Sur, San Francisco,
handles the creative duties.
</P>
