telephone company has caused angry protests, but more is at stake
than political symbolism or the efficiency of the telephone system.
Puerto Rico is under enormous pressure to hew more closely to the
capitalist road because it is losing special tax breaks and welfare
subsidies from Washington and because no island can remain an
island in the increasingly integrated global economy. By Peter
Passell.
