Yonkers spilled raw sewage into the Hudson River for more than 26
hours from Monday to Tuesday. Beaches are closed at
Croton-on-Hudson and Sleepy Hollow; workers are suspended and may
be fired for trying to cover up the fact that the accident
happened.
