<P>
   CIR-TESTS-ONLINE (Undated) _ Tired of cybersex and E-mail from
your relatives? What's left to do on line? Take tests. The web has
every imaginable test, from quick quizzes posted by Canadian Mensa,
to SAT's to riddles, puzzlers and personal nutrition
questionnaires. You can test your intelligence or your emotional
intelligence, and when you are done you can ponder why, after
suffering through years of tests in school, people still like to
take them for fun.
</P>
<P>
   With photo
</P>
<P>
   And
</P>
<P>
   CIR-VIDEOPHONES-MS (Undated) _ A look at Netmeeting, the
videoconferencing tool from Microsoft.
</P>
<P>
   And
</P>
<P>
   CIR-VIDEOPHONES-COMPARE (Undated) _ Comparing various models for
quality and cost.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-VIDEOPHONES (Undated) _ Videophones, a perennial dream of
futurists are here. But they're not so great. If grandparents
really wants to see the kids, or a face to face conversation is
important, they may be worth buying. A mass market, however, is
still in the future.
</P>
<P>
   With NETM, how people are really using Microsoft's Netmeeting
(for sending sexuual images of themselves back and forth), and
SVID, a graphic.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-GEEK-NOTES (Undated) _ Techno news and notes.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SLEEPLESS (Undated) _ Internet use interferes with not only
TV watching, but sleep.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-SANCTUM (Undated) _ Sanctum, a card collecting strategy
game, like Magic, The Gathering, but online, with virtual cards.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-VIKINGS (Undated) _ Vikings (norse warriors, not football
players) on line.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-BELIZE-CYBERCAFE (Undated) _ Cybercafe in Belize: farmers
and tourists get their e-mail.
</P>
