<HEADLINE>
SITE-SEEING: QUIZZES 
</HEADLINE>
   (Circuits)  
 (sidebar with cir-tests-online)  
 (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Web is full of tests of all sorts. Here's a sampling of
sites.
</P>
<P>
   EMOTIONAL INTELLIGENCE: www.utne.com/cgi-bin/eq Based on the
book, ``Emotional Intelligence'' by Daniel Goleman (Bantam, 1995).
</P>
<P>
   BRAIN TEASERS, RIDDLES AND OTHER TESTS: www.puzz.com
</P>
<P>
   NEW AGE I.Q. TEST: www.salemctr.com/iqtest.html
</P>
<P>
   THE KARMOMETER: www.randomhouse.com/lawoflove/karm.html.
Purports to give you a reading on how your karma is doing.
</P>
<P>
   MENSA: www.canada.mensa.org/mensa/workout.html. This test will
give you an initial screening for entrance into Mensa, at least the
Canadian branch.
</P>
<P>
   AN EASY I.Q. TEST: www.iqtest.com
</P>
<P>
   A DIFFICULT I.Q. TEST: cech.cesnet.cz/IQ/IQ-test-e.html
</P>
<P>
   A REAL PUZZLER: www.sinous.com/yao/braintest/12apples.html
</P>
<P>
   TEST FOR ATTENTION DEFICIT DISORDER:
www.med.nyu.edu/Psych/addc/addscr.htm
</P>
<P>
   BIBLE TEST: bibletutor.luthersem.edu
</P>
