<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 15:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6291 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SEDONA-SIDER-HNS &LR;      07-15 0708
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SEDONA-SIDER-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: SEDONA-OAK CREEK CANYON 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)    By HARRY SHATTUCK 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Advance planning: Call the Sedona-Oak Creek Canyon Chamber of
Commerce at 800-288-7336 to request free brochures. Access
http://www.arizonaguide.com/sedona on the Internet. Another good
online planning source is http://www.sedonabest.com
</P>
<P>
   When to go: Sedona is a year-round destination. The average
daily high temperature is 74.7 degrees (95.1 degrees in July, 55
degrees in January); the average low is 45.7 degrees (65.1 degrees
in July, 29.7 degrees in January). Average annual rainfall is 17
inches; average annual snow and sleet is 9 inches.
</P>
<P>
   Orientation: Numerous shops and restaurants and a visitor center
are situated in Uptown Sedona, just north of the intersection of
Highways 89A and 179. Other eateries and shops are scattered along
Highway 89A west toward Jerome. Most major art galleries, including
the Tlaquepaque Arts and Crafts Center, are located along Highway
179 to the south toward the Village of Oak Creek. The Oak Creek
Canyon scenic drive and recreation area is north of Uptown Sedona
(Highway 89A toward Flagstaff).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
LODGING: &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ Like Enchantment Resort, L'Auberge de Sedona has gained
national recognition. Conveniently located in Uptown Sedona in a
French country setting along the banks of Oak Creek, L'Auberge
features rooms in secluded cottages and in a European-style lodge.
Room size, styles and prices vary. Call 800-272-6777. Access
http://www.lauberge.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   _ Los Abrigados Resort &AMP; Spa is an all-suite Spanish-style
resort adjacent to Tlaquepaque Arts and Crafts Center. Call
800-521-3131.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Chamber of Commerce can provide information about motels
and hotels, B&AMP;Bs, condominiums, New Age-oriented lodgings, RV
resorts and private campgrounds. Call 800-288-7336. For information
about camping in the Oak Creek Canyon region, call 800-280-CAMP.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
DINING: &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Restaurants at L'Auberge de Sedona and Enchantment Resort are
elegant. Other options include Swiss, Thai, Italian, Chinese,
Indian, Japanese and Mexican restaurants. Within Oak Creek Canyon
and along Highway 89A, the rustic Junipine Resort's cafe proved a
comfortable and economical lunch stop. Numerous restaurant
brochures and sample menus are available at the Sedona Visitor
Center.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
TOURS: &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ Jeep tours are especially popular here. Separate tour focuses
include American Indian history and culture, vortexes, red-rock
photography and other subjects. Prices vary. Companies with a range
of offerings include Sedona Red Rock Jeep Tours (Call 800-848-7728
or 520-282-6826), Pink Jeep Tours (800-873-3662 or 520-282-5000),
Pink Jeep Tours Ancient Expeditions (800-999-2137 or 520-282-2137);
and Sedona Photo Tours (800-973 -3662 or 520-282-4320).
</P>
<P>
   _ Panoramic views of the rocks are available on tours by hot-air
balloon, helicopter or private airplane. Among options: Red Red
Rock Balloon Adventures (800-258-3754 or 520-284-0040); Sky High
Balloon Adventures (800-551-7597 or 520-204-1395); Northern Light
Balloon Expeditions (800-230-6222 or 520-282-2274); Skydance
Helicopters (800-882-1651 or 520-282-1651); Arizona Helicopter
Adventures (800-282-5141 or 520-282-0904); and Red Rock Biplane
Tours (888-766-7433 or 520-204-4939).
</P>
<P>
   _ Tours by bus and trolley are available. About 25 miles to the
south, the scenic Verde Canyon Railway (800-293-7245 or
520-639-0010) merits a side trip.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
GOLFING: &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Visitors are welcome at two picturesque 18-hole courses in the
Village of Oak Creek area. For details, contact the Sedona Golf
Resort at 520-284-9355 and Oak Creek Country Club at 520-284-0036.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Other telephone contacts:
</P>
<P>
   _ Sedona Arts Center: 520-282-3809
</P>
<P>
   _ Tlaquepaque Arts and Crafts Village: 520-282-4838.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sedona Ranger Station (a good resource for information about
Coconino National Forest activities): 520-282-4119.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sedona Parks and Recreation Dept. 520-282-7098.
</P>
<P>
   _ Slide Rock State Park: 520-282-3034.
</P>
<P>
   _ Red Rock State Park: 520-282-6907.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chapel of the Holy Cross: 520-282-4069.
</P>
