</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on...Antonio Banderas
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Antonio Banderas stars in ``The Mask of Zorro,'' opening Friday.
Other Banderas movies include:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Interview With the Vampire'': As the leader of the Paris
vampires in this Tom Cruise flick.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Philadelphia'': Helping boyfriend Tom Hanks deal with AIDS,
in a tear-jerker.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Miami Rhapsody'': Wooing Mia Farrow and daughter Sarah
Jessica Parker in this Woody Allen-ish comedy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Desperado'': Taking on a small-town crime boss in this
tongue-in-cheek action flick.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Assassins'': Trying to take out rival Sylvester Stallone.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Evita'': Singing and waltzing with Madonna.
</P>
<P>
   THE VIDEO COLLECTOR
</P>
<P>
   (Notable videos now on sale)
</P>
<P>
   Drama: ``Losing Chase,'' ``The Funeral,'' ``The Last Ride,''
$14.98. ``Julian Po,'' ``The Grass Harp,'' ``The Quiet Room,''
$19.98.
</P>
<P>
   Shakespeare: ``William Shakespeare's Romeo + Juliet''
(wide-screen edition), ``Twelfth Night,'' $19.98.
</P>
<P>
   Wide screen: ``Courage Under Fire,'' ``Predator,'' $19.98.
</P>
