<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    All ears
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL JULY 19: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   You just don't hear, ``Ooh, girl, those earrings are sharp,''
uttered as often or as enthusiastically as you used to.
</P>
<P>
   Close inspection of the latest looks in earwear proves that
``sharp'' doesn't apply at all. The more apt word to describe the
best earring styles out now is ``nice.''
</P>
<P>
   Nice as in: classy, compact, feminine and fuss-free.
</P>
<P>
   Fashionable ear wear doesn't cry out for attention by virtue of
its size, color or brilliance. Even the gemstone earrings currently
in style now manage to sparkle without screaming to be noticed.
</P>
<P>
   Factors to consider when choosing additions to your earring
wardrobe include:
</P>
<P>
   -- Does it hug the earlobe, rather than dangle daredevilishly
from it?
</P>
<P>
   -- Is it delicately crafted, or heavy-duty in construction?
</P>
<P>
   -- Are colored gemstones, pearls or crushed diamonds the focal
point of the earrings; or are they merely tried-and-true hoops or
studs?
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
