throughout the region once it is confident that its subsidiaries,
or partners, can deliver quality service. ``What we are trying to
do is put down roots. We're a Chilean bank in Chile and a Peruvian
bank in Peru,'' says Godsoe.
 &HT;    To critics who disagree with the bank's ``deliberate'' approach,
Godsoe says it will take time to see if the roots planted by
Scotiabank will take hold and flourish. ``Only in the long, long
run will we know,'' he says.
