<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   There have been previous animal-oriented quizzes, but few titles
are repeated here. (No, Gertrude Atherton's ``Black Oxen'' doesn't
appear this time!) Match title with author. You pass with a simple
majority of correct answers _ 11 _ and earn an A with 15 right.
Give yourself an additional point if you identify correctly the
novel whose movie version starred Robert Mitchum. Answers are on
the opposite page.
</P>
<P>
   The Literary Works:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Animal Farm''
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Ape and Essence''
</P>
<P>
   3. ``The Bat''
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Birds of America''
</P>
<P>
   5. ``The Bull From the Sea''
</P>
<P>
   6. ``Chicken Every Sunday''
</P>
<P>
   7. ``The Day of the Jackal''
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Dog Years''
</P>
<P>
   9. ``The Eagle Has Landed''
</P>
<P>
   10. ``Giles Goat-Boy''
</P>
<P>
   11. ``The Horse Whisperer''
</P>
<P>
   12. ``The Leopard''
</P>
<P>
   13. ``The Lion in Winter''
</P>
<P>
   14. ``Rabbit, Run''
</P>
<P>
   15. ``The Sea Wolf''
</P>
<P>
   16. ``Tiger at the Gates''
</P>
<P>
   17. ``The Track of the Cat''
</P>
<P>
   18. ``Turtle Diary''
</P>
<P>
   19. ``The White Monkey''
</P>
<P>
   20. ``Wild Animals I Have Known''
</P>
<P>
   Their authors:
</P>
