<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN LUIS (SAN LUIS, Sonora, Mexico) - It's been one year since a
crusading San Luis, Sonora, newspaper publisher was murdered.
Journalists from throughout northern Mexico converged on the
burgeoning border community. It is dangerous being a journalist in
Mexico these days and they are determined to change that, just as
they are determined to see that justice is served in the
newspaperman's murder. It is so dangerous that the publisher from
Tijuana, ambushed last year, decided not to make the trip, fearing
for his safety in San Luis. He is under constant guard, and his two
sons, photographers for the paper, wear bullet-proof vests and are
escorted round the clock by federal authorities trying to keep them
alive. Story will include some color from a graveside memorial
service for the slain publisher. By GRACIELA SEVILLA. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
COSMETIC KIDS (Undated) - Adult women aren't the only ones shelling
out for expensive lotions, potions and cosmetics. Young girls are
pouring into stores like Aveda and Bath &AMP; Body Works, giving the
stores a lucrative secondary market that they're tapping with
products and prices aimed at a younger crowd. By
</P>
<P>
   GLEN CRENO. Story will move in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
