Park each summer, straight through to Oct. 31 close of trout
season, crowds of anglers hammer Saddlebag, Tioga and Ellery lakes
and Lee Vining Creek on a daily basis. And for good reason. Each of
the waters have strong populations of wild brown, rainbow and brook
trout, and bi-weekly plants of catchable trout are made by the
Department of Fish and Game to ensure the fishery remains healthy.
However, if you come to the Eastern Sierra for solace and a
pristine mountain experience, that isn't what you'll likely find at
these instensely popular roadside jumping-off spots. The good news
is that solitude is just a short walk away, at Fantail Lake.
