<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 21:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7179 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBO-YANKEES-BOUTON-NY     07-15 0305
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBO-YANKEES-BOUTON-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AFTER ARTICLE BY SON, BOUTON INVITED BACK TO YANKEE STADIUM  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By BUSTER OLNEY    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT _ When Jim Bouton received a call Wednesday from someone
claiming to be with the Yankees, he was sure it was a friend
playing a joke. ``OK, who is this?'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, it was Joe Schillan, the promotions and events
coordinator for the Yankees, calling to ask Bouton to participate
in Old-Timers' Day at Yankee Stadium on July 25. ``It's been a very
emotional day here in our household,'' Bouton said from his home in
Egremont, Mass., the emotion he spoke of evident in his voice.
</P>
<P>
   Bouton won 39 games for the Yankees during the 1963 and 1964
seasons, but became persona non grata at Yankee Stadium after his
book ``Ball Four'' was published, containing details that shed
light on the off-the-field activities of the Yankee legend Mickey
Mantle and others.
</P>
<P>
   But on Father's Day of this year, Michael Bouton, his son, wrote
an article in The New York Times that was essentially a plea to the
Yankees to invite his father to Old-Timers' Day. Michael Bouton
noted the recent pain his family had suffered, following the death
last year of his sister, Laurie, in an automobile accident, and
suggested that it was time to forgive and forget.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees followed through, and Jim Bouton was touched. ``This
is the third time I've wept today and it's not even 2 p.m.,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Bouton's understanding Wednesday was that he would be introduced
wearing a suit, and would not play in the Old-Timers' Game. ``They
don't want anybody striking out the side,'' he said, joking. But a
member of the organization said Wednesday night that a uniform
would be made available to Bouton, and there was a possibility he
could play if he wished.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-15-98 2137EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
