<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-USAF-PILOT-TRAINING-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``When you send combat airplanes and crews into harm's way, if
they are going to survive and emerge victorious, they require
rigorous training day to day. In order to do that, you've got to
have a place for them to train.''
</P>
<P>
   _GEN. RICHARD HAWLEY, arguing for more training space for the
Air Force.
</P>
