   (NYT18) MOUNTAIN HOME, Idaho -- July 15, 1998 --
USAF-PILOT-TRAINING-2, 7-15 -- Terry Gibson, of the governing
council of the Shoshone-Pauite Tribes in the Duck Valley
Reservation in Idaho. Gibson says that the United States Air Force
does not appreciate the land's significance. ``To them, this is all
desolate -- rocks and scrub land,'' he says. ``But to us, this is
our bible.'' The Air Force is running into opposition from
ranchers, environmentalists, and Native Americans who believe the
roar of fast, low-flying jets is disrupting some of the nation's
last refuges of peace and quiet. (Glenn Oakley/New York Times
Photo)
